column23: seeds pale brown with white longitudinal striations and faint horizontal lamellae on sides and back, circa 2 mm long.
column24: an erect, perennial shrub to 2 m tall, foliose throughout.

column20: petioles circa 1 mm long; leaf blades oblanceolate, spathulate or linear-oblong, 9-35 mm long, 2-6 mm wide, l/b 4-11.5, base obtuse or cuneate, apex obtuse or acute often with a minute mucro.
column23: seeds pale brown, circa 1.5 mm long, muricate-striate, the back with longitudinal rows of tubercules, the sides with concentric rows.
column24: a blue-green, glabrous annual or biennial herb or subshrub to 70 cm tall.

column20: leaves almost sessile; blades narrowly lanceolate, linear-oblong, often obovate, 5-15 mm long, 3-5 mm wide, l/b 1.6-3.5, base obtuse, asymmetric, apex obtuse or acute often with a minute mucro.
column23: seeds brown, circa 2 mm long, the back with circa 20 rows of transverse ridges, the ridges and sides of the seed muricate.
column24: an erect, glabrous annual herb to 1 m tall with one main stem.

column20: all parts except upper surface of leaves rusty tomentose with short simple hairs and minute yellow fusiform vesicular medifixed glands. petioles 12-47 mm long. leaves discolorous, often whitish below; apparently simple, 45-100 mm long, 65-125 mm wide, l/w 0.7-0.9, cordate, emarginate, strongly palmately veined with a bristle in the sinus. inflores-cence racemose, axillary and terminal, to circa 65 mm long.
column23: seeds immersed in fibrous pith; dark brown, ellipsoid, slightly flattened, circa 4.5 mm long, 3.5 mm wide.
column24: deciduous, densely foliaged tree to 10 m high, usually smaller;

column20: leaves with petiole 2-10 mm long, channelled to grooved above, with ascending simple hairs and short crisp hairs; lamina ovate to lanceolate, obovate, widely to narrowly elliptic or oblong, 4.5-24 cm long, 2 -9 cm wide, base shallowly cordate or rarely rounded and more or less asymmetric, margins strongly undulate, apex acute to acuminate, discolorous, upper surface glossy and glabrous or glabrescent, lower surface with conspicuous oil glands and with scattered hairs along midrib and veins and often at the base.
column23: seeds circa 17 mm long, 10 mm wide, with longitudinal groove.
column24: shrub or tree to 25 m;

column20: cauline leaves opposite, rarely whorled, narrowly oblanceolate or linear, 2-5 mm long, 0.5-0.7 mm wide, glabrous to cobwebbed.
column23: seeds 11-27, brown, dimidiate, circa 0.4 mm long, 0.3 mm wide.
column24: compact perennial herb to 15 cm tall.

column20: cauline leaves opposite, rarely whorled, narrowly oblanceolate or linear, 2.3-9 mm long, 0.7-1.3 mm wide, glabrate.
column23: seeds circa 12, red-brown, more or less ellipsoid, circa 0.4 mm long.
column24: compact perennial herb to 15 cm tall.

column20: leaves imparipinnate; rachis to basal leaflets 15-47 mm, 67-130 mm overall; stipels absent; leaflets in 2-3 pairs, elliptic, ovate or rarely obovate, 55-125 mm long, 35-94 mm wide, l/w 1.3-1.9, base rounded, apex obtuse or shortly acuminate.
column23: seeds 1-2, light to dark brown, elliptic, circa 18 mm long, 11 mm wide;
column24: a deciduous tree to 10 m, sometimes taller, f lowering with the flush of new leaves;

column20: leaves pinnately 3-foliolate, 1-foliolate at base of plant, rachis to basal leaflets 5-15 mm, 9-20 mm overall; stipels persistent, filiform; leaflets dorsiventral, oblanceolate or obovate, (11)15-45 mm long, 6-25 mm wide, l/w 1.3-2.5(3); terminal leaflet usually larger than basals.
column23: seeds dark mottled, oblong, circa 4 mm long, 2 mm wide.
column24: erect or spreading perennial shrub with annual stems.

column20: leaf rachis to basal leaflets 12-42 mm, 20-55 mm overall; leaflets dark green, thin, ovate, base rounded, apex acuminate; basal leaflets 20-53 mm long, 11-34 mm wide, l/w 1.3-1.8; terminal leaflet 20-55 mm long, 15-45 mm wide, l/w 1-1.6.
column23: seeds 2, mottled red-brown, circa 4 mm long, 3 mm wide.
column24: slender twining or prostrate vine with annual stems and perennial roots.

column20: leaves blades linear, 4-14 mm long, 0.5-0.6 mm wide, l/b 8-23.
column23: seeds grey when mature, circa 8 mm long, with a thin firm spongy, irregularly pitted surface, margins sharply angled with irregular scallops.
column24: an erect, glabrous multistemmed subshrub to 50 cm tall.

column23: seeds flattened oblong, circa 5mm long, mottled, carunculate.
column24: an erect glabrous slender evergreen shrub to 1m tall.

column20: leaves termi-nated by a bristle, 5-8 pairs of leaflets, erect terete gland between lower 2-4 pairs of leaflets, rachis to basal leaflets 20-60 mm long, rachis 90-170 mm long; leaflets 5-8 pairs, elliptic to obovate, 20-50 mm long, 13-25 mm wide, l/w 1.6-2.3.
column23: seeds 12-26, transverse in pod, black, shiny, oblong to elliptic, 5-6 mm long, 2.7-3.5 mm wide, areole 0.9-1.2 mm wide.
column24: shrub or small glabrate tree to 7 m.

column20: leaf rachis 70-160 mm long; leaflets in 11-25 pairs, 6-19 mm long, 1.5-4 mm wide, l/w 4-6.6.
column23: seeds 23-40, olivaceous, mottled, circa 4 mm long, 2.2 mm wide.
column24: annual or short-lived perennial shrub to 3 m high.

column23: seeds pale brown, subglobular, circa 1 mm long, 1 mm wide;
column24: an erect annual or perennial shrub with + perennial rootstock, to 1 m tall.

column23: seeds 1-4, pale brown, ellipsoid, circa 7 mm long, 5 mm wide.
column24: perennial shrub to 1 m high, often with annual aerial parts. glabrate, hairs hyaline.

column24: annual, fleshy herb to 40 cm high, glaucous, glabrous;

column23: seeds 11-13 per pod, centres circa pod width apart, olivaceous, oblong, oblong in cross section, circa 2.1 mm long, 1.9 mm wide, ecarunculate.

column24: annual herb to 60 cm, glabrous, subglaucous.

column24: annual trailing or climbing vine, apparently dioecious (female flowers have not been observed);

column23: seeds pale and dark brown, + semicircular, circa 1.7 mm long, 1 mm wide.
column24: prostrate annual or (?) perennial rooted herb with annual stems. vegetative parts sparsely hairy with simple hairs;

column24: perennial, prostrate to decumbent herbs;

column23: seeds 23-53, brown or black, subcylindrical, 5.5-8 mm long, circa 3 mm wide.
column24: evergreen trees to 15 m high, probably short lived;
